The national assembly has set in a motion a process of amending the constitution that will see cabinet secretaries appointed from within elected members of parliament should the initiative become law. the constitution amendment bill number 40 of 2020, sponsored by the Ndaragwa mp Jeremiah Kioni led constitutional implementation oversight committee, is presently set for public participation scheduled for the next three weeks. Kioni has told KTN News that should everything go as planned, then the bill will become law by the end of the year.